This paper deals with the problem of crowdsourcing data labeling, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and information theory to optimize the labeling process, which falls under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of noise in the labeling process, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT).
